## 4. The "Hand Feel" Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Very firm, dense, substantial. (47.5-degree ESN sponge, but feels harder).
    - Feedback: Direct and raw. You feel exactly where you hit the ball on the blade.
    - Hold vs. Release: Massive hold. It feels like the ball sinks into the topsheet and stays there for an eternity before releasing.
    - Dwell Time: Extremely high for a rubber of this hardness, thanks to the flexible topsheet.

- Sound/Click
Produces a solid, deep thud rather than a high-pitched metallic click. It only "clicks" on the most powerful, perfectly timed shots.

