## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Perfect match. ALC or KLC outer blades (like the Viscaria or Timo Boll ALC) provide the crispness and speed needed to compensate for the rubber's linearity.
    - Inner Carbon: Good for spin-heavy styles, but might feel a bit slow or demanding from mid-distance.
    - All-Wood: Best paired with fast 7-ply woods (like Clipper Wood). Avoid 5-ply woods unless you want a purely close-to-table defensive/spin setup.
    - Mismatch Cases: Soft, slow 5-ply all-wood blades (results in a sluggish, overly demanding setup).

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Highly recommended. This is where most players have the physical mechanics to activate the MX-S properly.
    - Backhand: Only recommended for advanced players with elite backhand mechanics and strong wrists who can generate their own power.

